0 is the initial virus titer, k is the kinetic parameter (day−1), and t is the treatment time (d). The kinetic parameter k is usually expressed as D, which is also known as ‘decimal reduction time’ (time required to reduce initial virus titer by 90% or 1 log at a certain temperature) and was calculated as:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
